docs.text: this is director tim burton's finest film to date .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: many will compare this tale of martians who invade earth to independence day , but even though the stories are similar , they really are two distinctly different films .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however as a whole , mars attacks is much more entertaining than id4 , and i loved id4 .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: you really have to be in the right frame of mind to enjoy this film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it is completely wacked-out and unlike anything you've ever seen .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: once the silly tone of the film is set , it's easy to just sit back and throw logic out the window because logic and comedy just don't mix .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the plot is simple : martians invade the earth .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but it's different than any other invasion film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: usually it's the evil aliens versus the heroic humans .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this time however , it's the goofy aliens versus the equally goofy humans .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the martians , who are all computer generated , are just about the funniest things i've seen in a long time .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they look funny , they move funny , and their " language " is hilarious .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and about the special effects .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the effects in mars attacks !
docs.label: positive

docs.text: are just about the most flawless ones i've seen to date .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the computer animation of the martians combined with the goofy personalities they are given makes them seem 100% real .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are just a couple of scenes that don't work , mainly those involving sarah jessica parker and pierce brosnan on board an alien ship .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: also , glenn close overacts tremendously in her ( thankfully ) very limited screen time , so much so that i actually applauded silently when her character meets her demise .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but there are many big laughs in the film , as i said , if you are in the right mood .
